body.description: Why does most mouthwash burn and irritate? It actually doesn’t have to hurt to be effective. With CloSYS Mouthwashes you can protect your mouth from harmful bad breath germs and freshen your breath without the painful burn. CloSYS is one of the first mouthwashes to receive the American Dental Association seal for reducing bad breath. This gentle but powerful mouthwash is perfect for all ages because its patented formula is pH balanced and so gentle you’ll actually use it longer for better results. A 30-second rinse in the morning and evening after each brushing is easy, and all it takes to get great results. CloSYS Ultra Sensitive Mouthwash comes unflavored so it's like water and even tastes like water. But if you want to add your own flavoring it comes with an optional flavor dropper (mint) so you can add a little, a lot, or not at all. Nothing overpowering or painful. Just a clean, fresh, soothing mouthwash you’ll actually use, because CloSYS is the Gentlest Oral Care Ever.

CloSYS products are also free of sulfates, triclosan, and other harsh ingredients that can burn or irritate your mouth. reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 30, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Closys ULTRA SENSITIVE
reviews.reviewText: I bought this because I was told to and I listened. It is part of dental system where you use a list of products in sync. I do not know what it does specifically. I know children can use it and the ingredients are ok. I have noticed a change once I used all the products as recommended. If using it with everything else will keep me and my loved ones out of a dentists chair nothing else matters to me. *A little FYI you can get a weird taste in your mouth if used after eating certain foods. So try rincing with water first before use.*

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 24, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Be careful — tastes like water.
reviews.reviewText: I know.. Being careful of something that tastes like water, is a bit.. Odd.Though, if you’re super out of it and sleepy — make sure to be aware enough, to remember not to swallow.I haven’t swallowed it, though, I can see where someone might easily, accidentally do so, if they aren’t paying attention — I, certainly, have to stay mindful.Which, is nothing against the product, of course.More than anything, I am writing the review to say that it, truly, has no taste — other than being comparable to water.I use this mouth wash, as it was recommended by Dr. Ellie Phillips, on YouTube.I am on my fourth bottle, now — and I, definitely, notice a difference in my teeth/mouth, since starting her protocol.Certain areas no longer hurt or are as sensitive.So, I plan to continue to use this product.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 12, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars When using a product on your teeth it is a little hard to judge its effectiveness.
reviews.reviewText: The problem with a lot of items that you use on your teeth is that if it doesn't work, you won't be able to tell for a long time.That said, following the program associated with the product, my mouth feels very clean and fresh when I finish. That is what I can say, and I will keep using it.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 29, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great for those with sensitive gums
reviews.reviewText: I purchase this because I hate the mouthwash with alcohol and flavors. This brand is great because you can get it unflavored.It works well for those who have sensitive gums.Your breath smells fresh and clean.It does come with peppermint essential oil (food grade) that you can flavor the bottle to your liking. It's a large bottle too, so I feel like I'm getting a great deal on a mouthwash that works for my mouth.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 13, 2024
reviews.reviewText: The bottle top is much smaller on my bottle, with a flange on its base that was broken. There are no instructions as to dosage on the bottle, nor any visible markings to that effect on the top. The flavor dropper has very tiny instructions around its perimeter. I couldn't tell that its contents added any flavor to the mouthwash, even as a single drop in the filled top. The incredibly mild taste doesn't exactly inspire confidence that the product is doing anything for my oral hygiene, so don't trust my ratings as a user.
